ZH: 当你不知道真相的时候，不要随便说三道四。
EN: Don't spread rumors when you don't know the truth.

ZH: 他总是喜欢说三道四，给人留下坏印象。
EN: He always tends to gossip, which gives a bad impression.

ZH: 别听他说三道四，他只是在胡说八道。
EN: Don't listen to him spreading rumors, he's just talking nonsense.

ZH: 她喜欢说三道四，不喜欢直接跟人沟通。
EN: She enjoys gossiping and dislikes direct communication.

ZH: 别再跟我说三道四了，我已经知道真相了。
EN: Stop spreading rumors to me, I already know the truth.

ZH: 不要被他人的说三道四影响你的判断力。
EN: Don't let others' gossip affect your judgment.

ZH: 那家伙总是在背后说三道四，真令人气愤。
EN: That guy always talks behind people's backs, which is really infuriating.

ZH: 如果你只是为了娱乐而说三道四，那是很不负责任的。
EN: If you're spreading rumors just for entertainment, it's very irresponsible.

ZH: 别为了满足好奇心而说三道四。
EN: Don't spread rumors just to satisfy your curiosity.

ZH: 小心说三道四会导致人际关系的破裂。
EN: Be careful, gossiping can lead to the breakdown of relationships.

ZH: 她很讨厌别人在她背后说三道四。
EN: She dislikes it when people gossip about her behind her back.

ZH: 这个社交圈子总是充斥着说三道四的谣言。
EN: This social circle is always filled with rumors and gossip.

ZH: 我觉得我们应该停止说三道四，而是直接面对问题。
EN: I think we should stop gossiping and face the problem directly.

ZH: 那些总是说三道四的人往往是不被信任的。
EN: People who constantly gossip are often not trusted.

ZH: 不管别人怎么说三道四，我相信我朋友是无辜的。
EN: No matter what rumors are being spread, I believe my friend is innocent.

ZH: 那些说三道四的人只会招致别人的厌恶。
EN: Those who gossip will only bring about the dislike of others.

ZH: 对于那些总是说三道四的人我们应该保持警惕。
EN: We should be vigilant towards those who constantly gossip.

ZH: 说三道四只是浪费时间和精力。
EN: Gossiping is just a waste of time and energy.

ZH: 她总是在办公室里说三道四，影响了工作氛围。
EN: She always gossips in the office, which affects the work environment.

ZH: 他为了制造事端而故意说三道四，让人很气愤。
EN: He deliberately spreads rumors to stir up trouble, which is very infuriating.
